Day 4 – Flow Builder & Automation

What is Flow Builder?
Flow Builder is a Salesforce no-code automation tool used to automate business processes and reduce manual work.

--------------------------------------------------

Types of Flows

Screen Flow
- Requires user interaction
- Uses forms/screens
- Example: Student registration form

Record Triggered Flow
- Runs automatically
- No user interaction needed
- Example: Auto email after registration

--------------------------------------------------

Automation Ideas

1. Auto email after student registration
2. Auto update remaining seats
3. Notify faculty when course is full
4. Generate student ID automatically
5. Send fee deadline reminders

--------------------------------------------------

Flow Diagram

Student Registration Created
↓
Flow Trigger Starts
↓
Check Student Email
↓
Send Confirmation Email
↓
End

--------------------------------------------------

Manual vs Automated Process

Manual Process
Staff manually sends fee reminders.

Problems
- Time consuming
- Human errors
- Missed reminders

Automated Process
Salesforce automatically sends reminders before due date.

Benefits
- Saves time
- Faster communication
- Better productivity

--------------------------------------------------

Reflection

Automation helps companies:
- Save time
- Reduce errors
- Improve productivity
- Maintain consistency
- Automate repetitive tasks

--------------------------------------------------

Reflective Questions

Why do companies automate workflows?
To improve efficiency and reduce manual work.

What problems happen with manual processes?
Delays, mistakes, repeated work.

Difference between Screen Flow and Record Triggered Flow?
Screen Flow needs user interaction. Record Triggered Flow runs automatically.

Why is no-code automation powerful?
Businesses can automate without coding knowledge.

When should automation be avoided?
When human approval or decision-making is important.

How does automation improve consistency and productivity?
Automation performs tasks accurately and quickly every time.


